title.narrative: 002 PRIMARY HEALTH CARE CAPACITY FOR M

description.narrative: Primary healthcare system has capacity to provide quality package of essential maternal, newborn, child and adolescent health interventions at scale, focusing on underserved areas, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 improved and equitable coverage of quality health interventions for Newborns, Children, Adolescent girls and Women across the continuum of care at community and Primary Health Care (PHC) level

description.narrative: UNICEF focused not only on increasing quality of services but the continuity of services during the challenging COVID epidemic, prioritizing both upstream developments of critical strategies and guidelines and downstream adaptation of approaches to reaching the most underserved and at-risk communities, seeing a remarkable improvement in reaching coverage of skilled attendance, postnatal care and immunization despite the challenges. Quality will be a major focus of capacity building efforts moving forward, especially care arrangements during and immediately after delivery and filling gaps in routine immunization based on the immunization improvement roadmap. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:24/08/2020
